description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "Near Cork, in southern Ireland there stands old Blarney Castle. A myth says that Queens Elizabeth once referred to statements of the lord of this castle as just "blarney." With this there is the old prophecy that whoever would kiss a certain stone would be given persuasive power of speech."
